    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S featuring the iconic wide-body silhouette and integrated rear reflector strip. This example is powered by the 3.6L M96 naturally aspirated flat-six, delivering 320hp through a precise 6-speed longitudinal manual transaxle. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit and a rear main seal (RMS) replacement. The chassis remains taut with upgraded Bilstein B8 dampers paired with factory-spec Brembo four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. The viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system provides exceptional lateral grip and corner-exit traction. While showing minor patina consistent with its mileage, the engine pulls strongly through the entire rev range with no bore scoring symptoms and a clean oil analysis history. This is a driver-focused C4S ready for technical mountain passes.",
      "price": 36500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 48
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
